Anonymous Tue 20 Dec 2022 01:49:28 No.53141460 Report
Quoted By: >>53141493
>>53141362
It'd have to be possible, first. One of the central ideas of the Everett-Wheeler-Rhodes model is that any time anything could have happened in more than one way, the universe split into two branches where one happened in each. This holds right on down to things like radioactive decay events. The pathway from, say, the Miocene to a world with multiple intelligent anthro species, a world like ours except for that detail, is non-obvious to me. In our world all the proto-human species killed each other off, because they were competing for the same resources and the same ecological niche, until only our ancestors remained.
